<div class="container">
    <header>
        <h1>üìê Area of a Parallelogram</h1>
        <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.2rem;">Primary 4 Maths Lesson</p>
    </header>

    <hr>

    <section>
        <h2>1. The Magic Formula</h2>
        <p>To find the area of a parallelogram, we don't need complex math. We just need two numbers:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The <b>Base (b)</b>: The bottom line.</li>
            <li>The <b>Height (h)</b>: The straight line from top to bottom (like measuring how tall you are!).</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div style="text-align: center; background: #f1f1f1; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;">
            <h3>The Formula:</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 1.5rem;">$$Area = Base \times Height$$</p>
            <p style="font-size: 1.5rem;">$$A = b \times h$$</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>2. See it in Action!</h2>
        <p>Why is the formula the same as a rectangle? Click the button below to cut the triangle and move it!</p>
        
        <div class="animation-box">
            <svg width="500" height="200" viewBox="0 0 500 200">
                <text x="220" y="180" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="bold">Base</text>
                <text x="115" y="100" font-family="sans-serif" font-weight="bold" fill="#d81b60">Height</text>

                <path id="static-shape" d="M 150 50 L 350 50 L 350 150 L 150 150 Z" />

                <path id="moving-triangle" d="M 150 50 L 100 150 L 150 150 Z" />
                
                <line x1="150" y1="50" x2="150" y2="150" class="height-line" />
            </svg>

            <br>
            <button class="action-btn" onclick="toggleAnimation()">‚úÇÔ∏è Cut & Move Triangle!</button>
            <p id="anim-text">It looks like a parallelogram.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    

    <section>
        <h2>3. Your Turn to Practice</h2>
        
        <div class="exercise">
            <p><b>Question 1:</b> Base = 8 cm, Height = 5 cm.</p>
            <input type="number" id="q1" placeholder="Area?">
            <button onclick="checkAnswer(1, 40)">Check</button>
            <span id="fb1" class="feedback"></span>
        </div>

        <div class="exercise">
            <p><b>Question 2:</b> Base = 10 m, Height = 12 m.</p>
            <input type="number" id="q2" placeholder="Area?">
